# HTML Image Gallery

A simple image gallery built using HTML and CSS as part of my web development learning journey.  
This project demonstrates basic page structure, image rendering, flexbox layout, and responsive styling.

## Features

- Clean and simple HTML structure
- Flexbox-based gallery layout
- Clickable images that open in a new tab
- Responsive image scaling
- Easy-to-read CSS styling

## What I Learned

- How to structure an HTML page
- How to link external CSS files
- How to use flexbox (`display: flex`, `flex-wrap`, `justify-content`)
- How to work with relative file paths
- How to build a simple, reusable gallery component

## Preview

Open `helloworld.html` in your browser to view the gallery.

## How to Run

1. Clone or download the project
2. Open the folder in VS Code
3. Open `helloworld.html` in your browser
4. Enjoy the gallery

## Future Improvements

- Add hover animations
- Add a lightbox effect
- Make the gallery fully responsive
- Add thumbnails vs full-size images
